#!/bin/bash
# Display welcome message for installer mode

# Colors
BLUE='\033[0;34m'
GREEN='\033[0;32m'
YELLOW='\033[1;33m'
NC='\033[0m'

# Create welcome file for login banner
cat > /etc/motd << 'EOF'
================================================================================
     _   _ _ _   _                   ___  ____  
    | \ | (_) |_| |__  _ __ ___  _ __/ _ \/ ___| 
    |  \| | | __| '_ \| '__/ _ \| '_ \ | | \___ \
    | |\  | | |_| | | | | | (_) | | | |_| |___) |
    |_| \_|_|\__|_| |_|_|  \___/|_| |_\___/____/ 
                                                  
                    INSTALLATION MODE

Welcome to NithronOS Installation Environment!

To install NithronOS to your hard drive:

1. Login with:
   Username: user
   Password: live

2. Run the installer:
   $ sudo nithronos-installer

3. Follow the installation wizard

The installer will:
- Partition your disk (EFI + Btrfs)
- Install the base system
- Configure bootloader
- Set up NithronOS services

Need help? Visit: https://nithronos.org/docs/install
================================================================================
EOF

# Also display on current console
clear
cat /etc/motd
